				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-104a2ea elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="104a2ea" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
			<style>/*! elementor - v3.13.1 - 09-05-2023 */
.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-stacked .elementor-drop-cap{background-color:#69727d;color:#fff}.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-framed .elementor-drop-cap{color:#69727d;border:3px solid;background-color:transparent}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap{margin-top:8px}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap-letter{width:1em;height:1em}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap{float:left;text-align:center;line-height:1;font-size:50px}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap-letter{display:inline-block}</style>				<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The infrastructure of Lucidia is built on the powerful and advanced Unreal Engine 5 technology. Unreal Engine 5 is a game engine that can be used in many different industries and has been used successfully in the past. The Lucidia metaverse will use the Unreal Engine because it is flexible and has key features that are important for its success.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Simulation of physics</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The physics simulation system in Unreal Engine makes it possible for objects in the game world to interact in a realistic way. This includes dynamic collisions, object destruction, and ragdoll physics. This makes the game more realistic, which makes it more fun to play.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Animation</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The animation system of the engine lets developers make complex character movements and animations. This makes the game world feel more real and alive.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Artificial Intelligence</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The AI system in Unreal Engine lets developers make enemies that can make decisions and respond to what players do. This makes the game more interesting and challenging.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Graphics</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With features like real-time reflections, dynamic shadows, and physically-based rendering, Unreal Engine&#8217;s advanced graphics create a visually stunning and immersive game world that keeps players interested.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sound</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The engine&#8217;s audio system makes it easy to make realistic sound effects, music, and voiceovers, which are important for adding tension, atmosphere, and emotional impact to a game. This is especially important when Lucidia is used to host virtual events like concerts.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Multiplayer: Unreal Engine lets you play games with more than one person, which is a big part of the social experience of a metaverse.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tools</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tools like level design, animation, and scripting that come with Unreal Engine make it easier for developers to make and change game content. This saves them time and money and lets them focus on the creative parts of making games.</span></p><p> </p><p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Overall, the powerful features and capabilities of Unreal Engine 5 make it a great choice for building the Lucidia metaverse. This is because it gives users a realistic, engaging, and immersive experience while addressing common business problems like development time and cost.</span></p>						</div>
